A single-line shuttle train service is reportedly up-and-running from Germiston to Elandsfontein in a bid to alleviate inconvenience caused by the train crash on Thursday morning. EWN is reporting that Metrorail introduced the single-line train service and that the technical team was working to clear the line of all of the coaches and to repair the railway infrastructure. It was further reported that Metrorail hoped to resume its services as per normal by peak hour on Friday. ALSO READ: Metrorail trains collide in Joburg For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.